# Flutter Build-Time Configuration
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# This project uses --dart-define flags instead of a .env file.
# Flutter apps are compiled — there is no runtime .env loading.
#
# Pass these flags to `flutter run` or `flutter build`:
#
# USAGE EXAMPLES
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Windows desktop (development — default, no flag needed):
#   flutter run -d windows
#
# Android emulator:
#   flutter run -d android --dart-define=API_BASE_URL=http://10.0.2.2:5000/api/v1
#
# Android physical device (replace IP with your PC's local IP):
#   flutter run -d android --dart-define=API_BASE_URL=http://192.168.1.100:5000/api/v1
#
# Production APK build (replace with real server URL):
#   flutter build apk --dart-define=API_BASE_URL=https://api.your-server.com/api/v1
#
# Production Windows build:
#   flutter build windows --dart-define=API_BASE_URL=https://api.your-server.com/api/v1
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# AVAILABLE DART-DEFINE KEYS
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# API_BASE_URL   — Full base URL of the backend API (including /api/v1)
#                  Default: http://localhost:5000/api/v1
